{"lemma":"عَجَمُ","slug":"عَجَمُ","root":"ع.ج.م","root_slug":"ع-ج-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ج-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n28230","n28231","n28232"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"non-Arabs (as foreigners or barbarians)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Persians.","tags":["collective","historical"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bite, to chew"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to try, to test"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to point the text, to write distinguishing marks to it"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَجَمَ (ʕajama) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stones, kernels, pits, pips, fruit seeds","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ع ج م (ʕ j m). The word عَجَم (ʕajam, “non-Arabs”) is from a pre-Islamic form أَعْجَم (ʔaʕjam), from the root ع ج م (ʕ j m), referring to people who speak unclearly (thus reflecting the same semantic evolution as Ancient Greek βάρβαρος (bárbaros, “barbarian”))."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28230","headword_ar":"عَجْمٌ","root":"Ejm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young of camels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAt labuwn","text_ar":"بَنَات لَبُون"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiqaAq","text_ar":"حِقَاق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ji*aAE","text_ar":"جِذَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, S, * Msb, * TA:) thus far: (S, Msb:) when they have entered upon the state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ivonaA='","text_ar":"اـِثْنَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", they are of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jil~ap","text_ar":"جِلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: (IAar, TA:) applied to"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1967},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EujuwmN","text_ar":"عُجُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young camels of different ages not exceeding the age of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja*aE","text_ar":"جَذَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.)       -A2-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"root,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"base, of the tail;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) which is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSoEuS","text_ar":"عُصْعُص"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EujomN","text_ar":"عُجْمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajobN","text_ar":"عَجْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EujobN","text_ar":"عُجْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Msb;) [each] a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ejb","text_ar":"عجب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or, accord. to Lh, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ejb","text_ar":"عجب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajamN","text_ar":"عَجَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A4-  [Golius and Freytag have assigned to this word a meaning belonging to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajomiY~N","text_ar":"عَجْمِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","IAar","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n28231","headword_ar":"عُجْمٌ","root":"Ejm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph:       -A2-  and that here following."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n28232","headword_ar":"عَجَمٌ","root":"Ejm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Foreigners, as meaning"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"others than Arabs; such as are not Arabs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[often used as implying disparagement, like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barbarians;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and often especially meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persians;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, Mgh, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EujomN","text_ar":"عُجْمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [of which see an ex. in a verse of Lebeed cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAziqiY~N","text_ar":"رَازِقِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (S, Msb, K,) or this latter may be a pl. of the former: (TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajamiY~N","text_ar":"عَجَمِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojaAmN","text_ar":"اَعْجَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl., TA) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who is of the race of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajam","text_ar":"عَجَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"though he may be chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correct, in"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Arabic"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"denoting unity; but it is also the relative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and thus one may apply to an Arab the appellation ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajamiY~N","text_ar":"عَجَمِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning called thus in relation to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajam","text_ar":"عَجَم"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and one says also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN A^aEojamu","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ اَعْجَمُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man not of the Arabs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN A^aEojamu","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ اَعْجَمُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, not of the Arabs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"of dates (S, Mgh, Msb, K) and of the drupes of the lote-tree (Msb) and of grapes (Mgh, Msb) and of raisins and of pomegranates and the like, (Mgh,) or also of other things, (Msb,) or the similar stones of anything, (K,) or also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever is in the interior of a thing that is eaten such as the raisin and the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EujaAmN","text_ar":"عُجَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (K:) the vulgar say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajom","text_ar":"عَجْم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Yaakoob, S:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giyDN","text_ar":"غِيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in an explanation of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajamN","text_ar":"عَجَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is evidently, I think, used as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"(commonly termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jum~aAr","text_ar":"جُمَّار"},{"kind":"text","text":"q. v.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the palm-tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the n. un. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajamapN","text_ar":"عَجَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,) which is incorrectly expl. by AHn as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a grape-stone when it germinates."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, TA.)       -A3-  Also Camels"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that bite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chew, the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the tragacanths and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thorny trees, and satisfy themselves therewith so as to be in no need of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plants called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","Mgh"]}]}}